"title": "3248: Holy Spirit, conviction of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3248",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Holy Spirit convinces human beings of sin and of the reality of forgiveness through Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit convicts the world of sin and its consequences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:8-John16:11\">JHN 16:8–16:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Ways in which the Holy Spirit brings conviction</h2>\n<h3>Through preaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:14\">ACT 16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Through the exercise of spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:24-1Cor14:25\">1CO 14:24–14:25</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The reality of the Holy Spirit's conviction in the lives of believers</h2>\n<h3>He brings illumination</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17-Eph1:18\">EPH 1:17–1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:8-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:8–2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14-1Cor2:16\">1CO 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>He gives assurance about their new relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:16\">ROM 8:15–8:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>He convicts of the need for constant change</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:9\">ROM 8:5–8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:16–5:23</a></p>",
